<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-25T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.01/2062: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-26T00:00:00-04:00">April 26,
                                    1943—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>800. For Murphy. As suggested in final paragraph your 662, April 20, you
                            may endeavor informally to confirm your interpretation of certain points
                            in the Giraud Memorandum. You should not, of course, express any views
                            on the subject.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>